{
  "id": "helix-branch-protection",
  "title": "Add GitHub branch protection rules for main, staging, and dev",
  "category": "infrastructure",
  "description": "Add branch protection rules via GitHub API or `.github/` configuration to enforce:\n\n- `main`: Require PR, require all CI checks to pass, no force push, require linear history\n- `staging`: Require PR from `dev` only, require CI checks\n- `dev`: Require PR (from `feature/*`), require CI checks\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Use `gh api` to configure branch protection for `main`, `staging`, and `dev`\n2. Add a `docs/branch-protection.md` documenting what protections are in place and why\n3. Update `CONTRIBUTING.md` with branch workflow instructions for contributors\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Direct pushes to `main` and `staging` are blocked\n- All PRs to `main` require passing CI\n- Branch protection config is documented",
